"A group ontology that grounds perceived task objects (cups, cutlery, plate, toy blocks, basket) as typed, role-bearing, affordance-carrying individuals, so that an OWL DL reasoner can infer which objects are graspable."@en owl:sameAs "A group ontology that grounds perceived task objects (cups, cutlery, plate, toy blocks, basket) as typed, role-bearing, affordance-carrying individuals, so that an OWL DL reasoner can infer which objects are graspable."@en .

"A material object in the task environment that may be perceived, manipulated, used as a reference object, or assigned a task role."@en owl:sameAs "A material object in the task environment that may be perceived, manipulated, used as a reference object, or assigned a task role."@en .

"A physical object inferred to afford grasping by a robot end effector in the task context. Membership is derived by reasoning, not asserted."@en owl:sameAs "A physical object inferred to afford grasping by a robot end effector in the task context. Membership is derived by reasoning, not asserted."@en .

"A reduced educational ontology profile for semantic and affordance grounding of graspable objects in the AI Capstone 2026 course project."@en owl:sameAs "A reduced educational ontology profile for semantic and affordance grounding of graspable objects in the AI Capstone 2026 course project."@en .

"A reference object used for arranging cutlery in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "A reference object used for arranging cutlery in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"A robot component used to physically interact with objects, such as a gripper."@en owl:sameAs "A robot component used to physically interact with objects, such as a gripper."@en .

"A robot or robot-controlled agent that can perceive objects, reason over the ontology, and act in the task environment."@en owl:sameAs "A robot or robot-controlled agent that can perceive objects, reason over the ontology, and act in the task environment."@en .

"A role that an object plays within a task."@en owl:sameAs "A role that an object plays within a task."@en .

"A small object to be collected into the basket in the toy-block-collection task."@en owl:sameAs "A small object to be collected into the basket in the toy-block-collection task."@en .

"A task in which a robot changes the pose, state, or arrangement of physical objects."@en owl:sameAs "A task in which a robot changes the pose, state, or arrangement of physical objects."@en .

"A task role for an object that is directly acted upon or manipulated."@en owl:sameAs "A task role for an object that is directly acted upon or manipulated."@en .

"A task role for an object that receives or contains other objects."@en owl:sameAs "A task role for an object that receives or contains other objects."@en .

"A task role for an object that should be collected into another object or location."@en owl:sameAs "A task role for an object that should be collected into another object or location."@en .

"A task role for an object used as a spatial or semantic reference for arranging other objects."@en owl:sameAs "A task role for an object used as a spatial or semantic reference for arranging other objects."@en .

"AI Capstone 2026 Group 03"@en owl:sameAs "AI Capstone 2026 Group 03"@en .

"An action possibility associated with an object in relation to a robot capability and task context."@en owl:sameAs "An action possibility associated with an object in relation to a robot capability and task context."@en .

"An affordance by which an object can contain or receive other objects."@en owl:sameAs "An affordance by which an object can contain or receive other objects."@en .

"An affordance by which an object can participate in a stacking relation with another object."@en owl:sameAs "An affordance by which an object can participate in a stacking relation with another object."@en .

"An affordance by which an object can support the placement or arrangement of other objects."@en owl:sameAs "An affordance by which an object can support the placement or arrangement of other objects."@en .

"An affordance by which an object may be grasped, held, lifted, or repositioned by a robot gripper."@en owl:sameAs "An affordance by which an object may be grasped, held, lifted, or repositioned by a robot gripper."@en .

"Chun-yien Chang"@en owl:sameAs "Chun-yien Chang"@en .

