"Links an ontology individual to a coordinate frame or pose-frame identifier used in perception, reconstruction, or simulation."@en owl:sameAs "Links an ontology individual to a coordinate frame or pose-frame identifier used in perception, reconstruction, or simulation."@en .

"Records an approximate object width, which may be useful for checking whether an object fits within a gripper capability."@en owl:sameAs "Records an approximate object width, which may be useful for checking whether an object fits within a gripper capability."@en .

"Records the object label used by perception, simulation, or task documentation."@en owl:sameAs "Records the object label used by perception, simulation, or task documentation."@en .

"Records the perceived or assigned color of a physical object."@en owl:sameAs "Records the perceived or assigned color of a physical object."@en .

"Relates a physical object to an affordance associated with that object in the task context."@en owl:sameAs "Relates a physical object to an affordance associated with that object in the task context."@en .

"Relates a physical object to an end effector capable of manipulating it."@en owl:sameAs "Relates a physical object to an end effector capable of manipulating it."@en .

"Relates a physical object to the role it plays in a task."@en owl:sameAs "Relates a physical object to the role it plays in a task."@en .

"Relates a task to a physical object that is directly acted upon in that task."@en owl:sameAs "Relates a task to a physical object that is directly acted upon in that task."@en .

"Relates a task to a physical object used as a spatial or semantic reference."@en owl:sameAs "Relates a task to a physical object used as a spatial or semantic reference."@en .

"The baseline cup-stacking task instance for Group 03."@en owl:sameAs "The baseline cup-stacking task instance for Group 03."@en .

"The baseline cutlery-arrangement task instance for Group 03."@en owl:sameAs "The baseline cutlery-arrangement task instance for Group 03."@en .

"The baseline toy-block-collection task instance for Group 03."@en owl:sameAs "The baseline toy-block-collection task instance for Group 03."@en .

"The basket instance that receives toy blocks in the toy-block-collection task."@en owl:sameAs "The basket instance that receives toy blocks in the toy-block-collection task."@en .

"The blue cup instance for the baseline cup-stacking task."@en owl:sameAs "The blue cup instance for the baseline cup-stacking task."@en .

"The containment affordance of basket 01: the basket can receive and hold toy blocks; this is why the basket is a container rather than a grasp target."@en owl:sameAs "The containment affordance of basket 01: the basket can receive and hold toy blocks; this is why the basket is a container rather than a grasp target."@en .

"The fork instance for the baseline cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "The fork instance for the baseline cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"The grasping affordance of blue cup 01: the cup can be grasped, held, and lifted by the robot gripper."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of blue cup 01: the cup can be grasped, held, and lifted by the robot gripper."@en .

"The grasping affordance of fork 01: the fork can be grasped and repositioned by the robot gripper in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of fork 01: the fork can be grasped and repositioned by the robot gripper in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"The grasping affordance of knife 01: the knife can be grasped and repositioned by the robot gripper in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of knife 01: the knife can be grasped and repositioned by the robot gripper in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"The grasping affordance of pink cup 01: the cup can be grasped, held, and lifted by the robot gripper."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of pink cup 01: the cup can be grasped, held, and lifted by the robot gripper."@en .

"The grasping affordance of toy block 01: the block can be grasped and lifted by the robot gripper for collection into the basket."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of toy block 01: the block can be grasped and lifted by the robot gripper for collection into the basket."@en .

"The grasping affordance of toy block 02: the block can be grasped and lifted by the robot gripper for collection into the basket."@en owl:sameAs "The grasping affordance of toy block 02: the block can be grasped and lifted by the robot gripper for collection into the basket."@en .

"The knife instance for the baseline cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "The knife instance for the baseline cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"The pink cup instance for the baseline cup-stacking task."@en owl:sameAs "The pink cup instance for the baseline cup-stacking task."@en .

"The plate instance used as a placement reference in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en owl:sameAs "The plate instance used as a placement reference in the cutlery-arrangement task."@en .

"The robot end effector used to manipulate objects in Group 03's environment."@en owl:sameAs "The robot end effector used to manipulate objects in Group 03's environment."@en .

"The stackability affordance of blue cup 01: the cup can be stacked with another cup in the cup-stacking task."@en owl:sameAs "The stackability affordance of blue cup 01: the cup can be stacked with another cup in the cup-stacking task."@en .

"The stackability affordance of pink cup 01: the cup can be stacked with another cup in the cup-stacking task."@en owl:sameAs "The stackability affordance of pink cup 01: the cup can be stacked with another cup in the cup-stacking task."@en .

"The support affordance of plate 01: the plate can support cutlery placed on it; this is why the plate is a placement reference rather than a grasp target."@en owl:sameAs "The support affordance of plate 01: the plate can support cutlery placed on it; this is why the plate is a placement reference rather than a grasp target."@en .

"This ontology defines a compact course vocabulary for representing physical task objects, task roles, manipulation affordances, grounding identifiers, and inferable graspability in the AI Capstone 2026 Physical AI project."@en owl:sameAs "This ontology defines a compact course vocabulary for representing physical task objects, task roles, manipulation affordances, grounding identifiers, and inferable graspability in the AI Capstone 2026 Physical AI project."@en .

